stories.text:
Searching for "Russia Today" or "Sputnik News" doesn't return their URLs, but does return other related links. Seems to be related to a gov request: https://lumendatabase.org/notices/26927483#.

It's not a court order, so Google voluntarily decided to implement this.

Mildly interesting; I don't think anyone is surprised.
stories.title: Tell HN: Google removes Russian news from results

stories.text:
Clipboard managers are an essential tool for me.

On windows I used Ditto.

On linux I used CopyQ.

But after a while I started encountering issues.

So I made my own manager based on rofi.

If you have linux and rofi this might work nicely for you.

It consists of a small c program and a python script.

https://github.com/madprops/clipton
